{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Goal\nPrevent future Codex sessions from treating a curl --netrc 401 as proof that working Gerrit HTTPS credentials are invalid.\n\n## Implementation\n- Edit the Codex Gerrit workflow rule in AGENTS.md because Codex loads that file at session start. Document that authenticated /a/ REST polling must obtain the username and password through git credential fill when the checkout uses a Git credential helper; curl --netrc is only valid when .netrc was explicitly configured.\n- Provide a shell pattern that keeps credentials in variables, passes them directly to curl, and never echoes or logs the password. Keep the existing git push and Gerrit gate guidance unchanged.\n- Extend tests/unit/test_codex_agent_guidance.py with assertions for git credential fill, curl --netrc, the false-401 explanation, and the no-echo requirement.\n\n## Verification\nRun env PATH=\"$PWD/.venv/bin:$PATH\" python -m pytest tests/unit/test_codex_agent_guidance.py and env PATH=\"$PWD/.venv/bin:$PATH\" make check.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] AGENTS.md tells non-interactive Codex to use git credential fill for authenticated Gerrit /a/ REST calls when Git credentials are stored in the configured helper.\n- [ ] AGENTS.md explains that curl --netrc returning 401 does not invalidate credentials already proven by git-over-HTTPS unless .netrc was explicitly configured.\n- [ ] The documented example never prints or logs the password and preserves the existing git push guidance.\n- [ ] tests/unit/test_codex_agent_guidance.py enforces the new guidance and passes.","parent_id":""}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784752075614603001,"uuid":"36476929-b462-45c3-a16d-1f60619f559e"}